    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I also prefer the dialog variant because all actions are explicit. A minor downside is that it adds a step to the process which could make remapping multiple keys a little cumbersome.\r\n\r\nI was actually thinking about moving both the _Reset_ and _Clear_ buttons out of the input and putting them next to _OK_ and _Cancel_. Like so:\r\n![default](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1355810/50729070-24864500-113c-11e9-9bff-1846dcabf7cd.png)\r\n\r\nAlso thought about labeling all of the buttons, but that takes a lot of space and feels a little overwhelming:\r\n![default](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1355810/50729131-27ce0080-113d-11e9-9d38-961a2a566ae4.png)\r\n\r\nOr only the _Reset_ (default) button and leaving the _Clear_ button in the input:\r\n![default](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1355810/50729158-a9be2980-113d-11e9-8bbc-d4dfda878304.png)\r\n"
